<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Assumptions — {{FEATURE_NAME}}</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="spec.css">
</head>
<body>
<div class="page-wrap">

  <nav class="sidebar" aria-label="Table of contents">
    <p class="sidebar-title">Contents</p>
    <div id="toc-list"></div>
  </nav>

  <div class="main-content">
    <header class="spec-header">
      <h1>Assumptions — {{FEATURE_NAME}}</h1>

      <table class="meta-table">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>Feature</th>         <td><code>{{FEATURE_NAME}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Feature slug</th>    <td><code>{{FEATURE_SLUG}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Source document</th> <td><code>{{SOURCE_DOCUMENT}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Task ID</th>         <td><code>{{TASK_ID}}</code></td></tr>
          <tr><th>Created</th>         <td><code>{{CREATED_DATE}}</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </header>

    <main>

      <section id="purpose">
        <h2>Purpose</h2>
        <p>This document records assumptions made while converting the source material into an SDD spec.</p>
        <p>Assumptions are not hidden decisions. They must be explicit, reviewable, and either accepted, corrected, or removed before implementation.</p>
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="assumption-status-summary">
        <h2>Assumption status summary</h2>

        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Risk level</th><th style="text-align:right">Count</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Low</td>    <td style="text-align:right">{{LOW_RISK_COUNT}}</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Medium</td> <td style="text-align:right">{{MEDIUM_RISK_COUNT}}</td></tr>
            <tr><td>High</td>   <td style="text-align:right">{{HIGH_RISK_COUNT}}</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p><strong>Blocking assumptions present:</strong></p>
        <pre><code>{{BLOCKING_ASSUMPTIONS_PRESENT}}</code></pre>
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="assumptions">
        <h2>Assumptions</h2>

        <!-- Repeat this card block for each assumption.
             Add class="risk-high", "risk-medium", or "risk-low" to .card based on risk level. -->
        <div class="card risk-high" id="a1">
          <div class="card-header">
            <span class="req-id">A1</span>
            <span class="card-title">{{ASSUMPTION_TITLE}}</span>
            <span class="badge badge-pending">Pending</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <dl class="card-fields">
              <dt>Assumption</dt>            <dd>{{ASSUMPTION_TEXT}}</dd>
              <dt>Reason</dt>                <dd>{{ASSUMPTION_REASON}}</dd>
              <dt>Risk level</dt>            <dd>{{RISK_LEVEL}}</dd>
              <dt>Impact if wrong</dt>       <dd>{{IMPACT_IF_WRONG}}</dd>
              <dt>Blocks implementation</dt> <dd>{{BLOCKS_IMPLEMENTATION}}</dd>
              <dt>Related requirements</dt>  <dd>{{RELATED_REQUIREMENT}}</dd>
              <dt>Related design sections</dt><dd>{{RELATED_DESIGN_SECTION}}</dd>
              <dt>Review status</dt>         <dd><span class="badge badge-pending">Pending</span></dd>
              <dt>Developer decision</dt>    <dd>Pending</dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>

      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="accepted-assumptions">
        <h2>Accepted assumptions</h2>
        <p>Move assumptions here after the developer explicitly accepts them.</p>
        <!-- Example accepted assumption:
        <div class="card risk-low" id="a1-accepted">
          <div class="card-header">
            <span class="req-id">A1</span>
            <span class="card-title">Default result limit</span>
            <span class="badge badge-ok">Accepted</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <p>Accepted by developer on YYYY-MM-DD.</p>
            <p><strong>Decision:</strong> The default result limit is 5.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        -->
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="rejected-or-replaced-assumptions">
        <h2>Rejected or replaced assumptions</h2>
        <p>Move assumptions here when the developer rejects or replaces them.</p>
        <!-- Example rejected assumption:
        <div class="card risk-medium" id="a2-rejected">
          <div class="card-header">
            <span class="req-id">A2</span>
            <span class="card-title">Empty-state copy</span>
            <span class="badge badge-rejected">Rejected</span>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <p>Rejected by developer on YYYY-MM-DD.</p>
            <p><strong>Original assumption:</strong> Use "No notes found."</p>
            <p><strong>Replacement decision:</strong> Use "You do not have any notes yet."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        -->
      </section>

      <hr>

      <section id="notes-for-claude-code">
        <h2>Notes for Claude Code</h2>
        <div class="claude-note">
          <h4>Rules Claude Code must follow</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>Do not implement while any assumption has <strong>Blocks implementation: Yes</strong> and <strong>Review status: Pending</strong>.</li>
            <li>Do not treat assumptions as approved unless the developer explicitly accepts them.</li>
            <li>If an assumption affects security, permissions, data deletion, billing, public API behavior, or irreversible migrations, prefer moving it to <code>open-questions.html</code>.</li>
            <li>If the implementation requires a new assumption, stop and update this file before proceeding.</li>
            <li>If assumptions contradict <code>requirements.html</code>, <code>design.html</code>, or developer instructions, stop and ask for clarification.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div><!-- /.main-content -->
</div><!-- /.page-wrap -->
<script src="spec.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
